<item>
            <title>[SPARK-13958] Executor OOM due to unbounded growth of pointer array in Sorter</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SPARK-13958</link>
                <project id="12315420" key="SPARK">Spark</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;While running a job we saw that the executors are OOMing because in UnsafeExternalSorter&apos;s growPointerArrayIfNecessary function, we are just growing the pointer array indefinitely. &lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/util/collection/unsafe/sort/UnsafeExternalSorter.java#L292&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/blob/master/core/src/main/java/org/apache/spark/util/collection/unsafe/sort/UnsafeExternalSorter.java#L292&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This is a regression introduced in PR- &lt;a href=&quot;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/11095&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://github.com/apache/spark/pull/11095&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
</description>
